Welcome to pythonautoimport!

Pythonautoimport is a simple python function for automatic import
packages into all modules of a program, which could be very useful 
in interactive debugging process. This module avoids you to enter long
import instructions at every break point.

ModulesLoader.py also contains load_scientific_modules() function which
helps you to debug scipy programs in Matlab style.

Just enter:

x = np.arange(0.0, 1.0+0.01, 0.01)
y = np.cos(2*2*np.pi*x)
plt.plot(x, y)
plt.show()

At a debug point to visualize your data.


